Setup / execution guide (Windows PowerShell, current state)
Use screen_analyzer_v1/ as the canonical runtime root.

From repository root:

Set-Location .

Create venv + install:

python -m venv .\screen_analyzer_v1\.venv
.\screen_analyzer_v1\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
pip install -r .\screen_analyzer_v1\requirements.txt

Set key:

$env:OPENAI_API_KEY="..."

Config/schema locations:

runtime config: 002_config/002.002_runtime_settings.yaml

prompt config: 002_config/002.001_prompt_settings.yaml

schema: 003_schemas/003.001_screen_analysis_schema.json

(Optional) Edit 002_config/002.002_runtime_settings.yaml

confirm camera.source
confirm capture.interval_seconds: 3

Smoke camera:

python .\screen_analyzer_v1\005_scripts\005.002_smoke_capture.py --source 0 --output-dir .\screen_analyzer_v1\008_outputs\smoke

Single-frame API check:

python .\screen_analyzer_v1\005_scripts\005.001_single_frame_analysis.py --image .\screen_analyzer_v1\008_outputs\smoke\<frame>.jpg

Run full app:

python .\screen_analyzer_v1\001_app\002_app_entrypoint.py

Monitor artifacts:

snapshots: screen_analyzer_v1/008_outputs/snapshots/
logs: screen_analyzer_v1/010_logs/runtime.jsonl
